        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-13T20:20:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, we could let this get pretty arbitrarily large. I was mostly concerned with pathological loops triggering timeouts during loop unrolling in the VM backend. On very bad ES2 devices, int could easily be limited to ~1k. Of course, this loop count limit is really separate from that:\n\nfor (float x \u003d 0; x \u003c 1; x +\u003d 0.00001) { ... }",
      "parentUuid": "c8d7114f_c46d1ccb",
      "revId": "e500a282659655c3e70bb8e88cf5c4b2416f2b31",
